<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1764,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,454,1800,1827]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Original description:</emphasis>
not described. This taxon was never formally described, but only figured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini (1902a)</bibRefCitation>
under the name “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Monterosato" authorityName="Monterosato" box="[446,1102,1836,1863]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="coralligena">
<emphasis box="[446,660,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Bittium iadertinum</emphasis>
Brusina var. 
<emphasis box="[816,945,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">coralligena</emphasis>
Monterosato
</taxonomicName>
”. Monterosato also never described this taxon (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Appolloni, M. &amp; Smriglio, C. &amp; Amati, B. &amp; Luglie, L. &amp; Nofroni, I. &amp; Tringali, L. P. &amp; Mariottini, P. &amp; Oliverio, M." box="[409,655,1872,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref15382" refString="Appolloni, M., Smriglio, C., Amati, B., Luglie, L., Nofroni, I., Tringali, L. P., Mariottini, P. &amp; Oliverio, M. (2018) Catalogue of the primary types of marine molluscan taxa described by Tommaso Allery Di Maria, Marquis of Monterosato, deposited in the Museo Civico di Zoologia, Roma. Zootaxa, 4477 (1), 1 - 138. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4477.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Appolloni 
<emphasis box="[531,588,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), and thus this name is available due to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1107,1270,1872,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini (1902)</bibRefCitation>
’s figures, published before 1931 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[374,508,1909,1935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 11, 12).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1764,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,435,1944,1971]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Material examined:</emphasis>
15 shells labelled by Bellini “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Mtros-Capri" authorityName="Mtros-Capri" box="[775,1427,1944,1971]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="coralligenum">
<emphasis box="[775,988,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Bittium iadertinum</emphasis>
Brus. 
<emphasis box="[1062,1259,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">var. coralligenum</emphasis>
Mtros—Capri
</taxonomicName>
” (MCZR—not numbered) actually belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Brusina, 1865" authorityName="Brusina" authorityYear="1865" box="[657,1042,1980,2007]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jadertinum">
<emphasis box="[657,871,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Bittium jadertinum</emphasis>
Brusina, 1865
</taxonomicName>
, now a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(da Costa, 1778) (MolluscaBase 2019 c)" authorityName="da Costa" authorityYear="1778" baseAuthorityName="da Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1778" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Bittium reticulatum</emphasis>
(da Costa, 1778) (MolluscaBase 2019c)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[747,868,2016,2043]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1460,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,395,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,414,1432]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Bittium iadertinum var. coralligena. A. Original figures. B. Possible type material from Capri Island (Naples)—4.9×1.5 mm. C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCZR—not numbered. D, E. Murex trunculus var. propeconglobata. D. Fossil(?) shell from Sciacca (Agrigento)—72.4×52.8 mm. E. Original label handwritten by Monterosato. MCZR- M-7623. F, G. Fusus (Pseudofusus) pulchellus var. curta. F. Original figures. G. Shells from Capri Island (Naples) and original label handwritten by Monterosato (up to 16 mm in total height). MCCIC—drawer 8, n. 146. H. Clathromangilia granum var. prausi. Original figures. I. Left. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. minimum. Original figure. I. Right. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. paludosum. Original figures." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449572/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="353" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,153,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a 
<taxonomicName box="[621,787,152,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="connected">race connected</taxonomicName>
to a specific habitat, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[213,348,189,215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). Strangely, 
<bibRefCitation author="Praus Franceschini, C." box="[692,988,188,215]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref18743" refString="Praus Franceschini, C. (1906) Elenco delle conchiglie del Golfo di Napoli e del Mediterraneo esistenti nel Museo Zoologico di Napoli. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 2 (5), 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="1906">Praus Franceschini (1906)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1255,188,215]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="coralligena">
var. 
<emphasis box="[1126,1255,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">coralligena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Payraudeau, 1826)" authorityName="Payraudeau" authorityYear="1826" baseAuthorityName="Payraudeau" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[151,563,224,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="latreillei">
<emphasis box="[151,336,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Bittium latreillei</emphasis>
(Payraudeau, 1826)
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Mtrs." authorityName="Mtrs." box="[627,870,224,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="corallinum">
var. 
<emphasis box="[678,801,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">corallinum</emphasis>
Mtrs.
</taxonomicName>
” as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Brusina, 1865" authorityName="Brusina" authorityYear="1865" box="[1053,1432,224,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jadertinum">
<emphasis box="[1053,1265,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Bittium jadertinum</emphasis>
Brusina, 1865
</taxonomicName>
, thus raising doubts as to whether or not he cited the taxon introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[956,1129,260,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini (1902a)</bibRefCitation>
. Material belonging to both taxa was deposited in the MZF2 museum by himself, thus not constituting the original 
<typeStatus box="[1155,1218,297,323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">types</typeStatus>
; such material was also not found by us in MZF2. Also 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[571,742,332,359]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini (1929a)</bibRefCitation>
only listed 
<taxonomicName box="[879,1274,332,359]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="corallinum">
<emphasis box="[879,1093,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Bittium iadertinum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1151,1274,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">corallinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his general overview of the marine molluscan species living in the Gulf of Naples, thus apparently skipping his own taxon. No other mention to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1902 a" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1902" box="[385,947,404,431]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="iadertinum" variety="coralligena">
<emphasis box="[385,597,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Bittium iadertinum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[653,782,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">coralligena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[789,947,404,431]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini, 1902a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was found in the subsequent malacological literature. Taking into account the complex taxonomy of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1847" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[915,1134,441,467]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cerithiidae" genus="Bittium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,997,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Bittium</emphasis>
Gray, 1847
</taxonomicName>
, as well as the low quality of the original figures, this taxon may fit several congeneric Mediterranean taxa, and thus it is considered a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">nomen dubium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[250,384,513,539]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: glossary).
</paragraph>
